sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K165001
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: John Szymanski
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is the GAL1 inducible promoter for use in Saccharomyces cerevisiae. It is repressed in the presence of glucose and induced in the presence of galactose. Raffinose is a neutral sugar source the neither induces nor represses the promoter. pGAL1 normally has an "all-or-nothing" response to galactose, but Christina Smolke has shown that knockout of the Gal2 gene gives pGAL1 a tunable, linear response to galactose.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: From the Saccharomyces cerevisiae genome, via Caroline Ajo-Franklin.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K105027
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Michael Wild
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is the core of the CYC1 promoter of ''S. cerevisiae''. This promoter element allows basal transcription. The transcription signal can be modulated by adding operator sites upstream of this BioBrick. In that way activators or repressors can act on the transcription machinery.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: This BioBrick contains the TATA-box and most of the 5'UTR (-139 to -36, relative to the translational start)of the natural CYC1 promoter. A Kozak sequence is not included and has thus to be added!

This BioBrick contains the TATA-box with one point mutation and most of the 5'UTR (-139 to -36, relative to the translational start) of the natural CYC1 promoter. A Kozak sequence is not included and has thus to be added!

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_M31201

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Katherine Aull
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
Description of CLB1 (from SGD): B-type cyclin involved in cell cycle progression; activates Cdc28p to promote the transition from G2 to M phase; accumulates during G2 and M, then targeted via a destruction box motif for ubiquitin-mediated degradation by the proteasome.
More information found here: http://db.yeastgenome.org/cgi-bin/locus.pl?locus=CLB1
